def: A genus of Spherobacteria, in the form of very small globularor oval cells, forming, by transverse division, filaments, or chainsof cells, or in some cases single organisms shaped like dumb-bells(Diplococcus), all without the power of motion. See Illust. ofAscoccus.
Bearing sarments, or runners, as the strawberry.
A pike when full grown. Halliwell.

Resembling spar, or consisting of spar; abounding with spar;having a confused crystalline structure; spathose. Sparry iron(Min.), siderite. See Siderite (a).-- Sparry limestone (Min.), a coarsely crystalline marble.
The state of being deplored or deplorable. [R.] Bp. Hail.
To reject by judicial sentence; also, to abjudge. [Obs.] Ash.
A shoe for oxen, consisting of a flat piece of iron nailed tothe hoof.
